collapsed.description: Rule that fires if an expression is visually abstracted

blank-cell-empty.description: Blank cell in a table or matrix

blank-line-empty.description: Blank line in a equation list or case statement

font-number.description: Explicit speaking of font for numbers

number-with-chars-brief.description: A number that contains letters in brief and super brief style

number-as-upper-word.description: A number that consists exclusively of characters

number-baseline.description: A number that follows directly an identifier has to be explicitly separated with a baseline indicator as not to be confused with a simple subscript.
number-baseline.example: t0 is pronounced t baseline zero. In contrast a_0 is pronounced a zero.

number-baseline-brief.description: A number that follows directly an identifier has to be explicitly separated with a brief baseline indicator as not to be confused with a simple subscript.
number-baseline-brief.example: t0 is pronounced t base zero. In contrast a_0 is pronounce a zero.

number-baseline-font.description: A number with unusual font that follows directly an identifier. Has to be explicitly separated with a baseline indicator and its font.

number-baseline-font-brief.description: A number with unusual font that follows directly an identifier. Has to be explicitly separated with a brief baseline indicator and its font.

negative-number.example: negative five, negative a, negative one half

negative.description: Minus as a prefix operator or sign of a complex expression
negative.example: Cases that are not covered by negative-number rule

parameters.%1: List of components of the subtraction

fences-neutral.example: begin absolute value A end absolute value

fences-neutral-sbrief.description: Absolute value of an expression in super brief style
fences-neutral-sbrief.example: absolute value A end absolute value

fences-metric-sbrief.description: Metric of an expression in super brief style

fences-set.example: begin set a , b, c end set

fences-set-sbrief.description: A set expression in super brief style
fences-set-sbrief.example: set a , b, c end set

minus.description: The minux sign (not as a unary operator)

vulgar-fraction.description: Rule for speaking a vulgar fraction in words

continued-fraction-outer.description: The outer part of a continuous fraction
continued-fraction-outer.example: ContinuedFraction a Over 1 plus StartFraction b Over 2 plus StartFraction 1 plus c Over ellipsis

continued-fraction-outer-brief.description: The outer part of a continuous fraction in brief and super brief style
continued-fraction-outer-brief.example: ContinuedFrac a Over 1 plus StartFraction b Over 2 plus StartFraction 1 plus c Over ellipsis

continued-fraction-inner.description: The inner part of a continuous fraction

continued-fraction-inner-brief.description: The inner part of a continuous fraction in brief style

continued-fraction-inner-sbrief.description: The inner part of a continuous fraction in super brief style

integral-brief.description: An integral with boundaries in brief and super brief style

parameters.%2: The squaring expression (only used for grammatical purposes)
The prime operator. As there are multiple prime operators (from single to quadruple) they are pronounciation is handled seperately.

prime.description: Primed expression with one, two, three, multiple primes

counted-prime.description: A counted prime expression with counter >= 5

counted-prime-multichar.description: A counted prime expression with counter >= 5. Similar to counted-prime but operates by counting single elements in a string

overscore.description: Expression modified above with an accent-like symbol
overscore.example: modifying above b with right arrow

overscore-brief.description: Expression modified above with an accent-like symbol in brief and super brief style
overscore-brief.example: mod above b with right arrow

double-overscore.description: Expression modified above with two accent-like symbols
double-overscore.example: modifying above above modifying above b with right arrow with left arrow

double-overscore-brief.description: Expression modified above with two accent-like symbols in brief and super brief style
double-overscore-brief.example: mod above above mod above b with right arrow with left arrow

underscore.description: Expression modified below with an accent-like symbol
underscore.example: modifying below y with left arrow

underscore-brief.description: Expression modified below with an accent-like symbol in brief and super brief style
underscore-brief.example: mod below y with left arrow

double-underscore.description: Expression modified below with two accent-like symbols
double-underscore.example: modifying below below modifying below y with left arrow with right arrow

double-underscore-brief.description: Expression modified below with two accent-like symbols in brief and super brief style
double-underscore-brief.example: mod below below mod below y with left arrow with right arrow

parameters.%1: The single cells of the row

row-with-label.description: A labelled row in a multi equation table.

row-with-label-brief.description: A labelled row in a multi equation table in brief and super brief reference

row-with-text-label.description: A row in a multi equation table labelled by text, i.e., parentheses are not spoken

empty-cell.description: An empty cell in a table or matrix

determinant.description: A determinant given in barred fences

determinant-sbrief.description: A determinant given in barred fences read in brief or super brief style

determinant-simple.description: A determinant given in barred fences with simple elements, i.e., columns will not be explicitly pronounced

determinant-simple-sbrief.description: A determinant given in barred fences with simple elements, i.e., columns will not be explicitly pronounced in brief and super brief style

layout.description: A layout structure, e.g., a large equation table.

layout-sbrief.description: A layout structure, e.g., a large equation table. In brief and superbrief style.

binomial.description: A binomial or two dimensional vector

binomial-brief.description: A binomial or two dimensional vector in brief style

binomial-sbrief.description: A binomial or two dimensional vector in super brief style

parameters.%2: The lines of the case statement

cases.description: A case statement with singular large fence for combining cases

parameters.%2: The lines of the case statement

cases-brief.description: A case statement with singular large fence for combining cases in brief style

parameters.%2: The lines of the case statement

cases-sbrief.description: A case statement with singular large fence for combining cases in super brief style

line-with-label.description: A line (mainly in case statements) with a label

line-with-label-brief.description: A line (mainly in case statements) with a label in brief and super brief style

line-with-text-label.description: A line (mainly in case statements) with a text label, where parentheses would not be spoken

empty-line-with-label.description: An empty line (mainly in case statements) with a label

empty-line-with-label-brief.description: An empty line (mainly in case statements) with a label in brief or super brief style

parameters.%1: The enclosing structure (e.g., a box, circle). This programmatically translated.

enclose.example: start enclose box x + y end enclose

leftbar.description: Elements with an attached left bar

rightbar.description: Elements with an attached right bar

crossout.description: A struck out or crossed out expression

cancel.description: An expression that is crossed out an replace by one above it

cancel-reverse.description: An expression that is crossed out an replace by one below it

parameters.%1: The name of the inference rule

multi-inference.description: An inference rule with two or more premises

parameters.%1: The name of the inference rule

inference.description: An inference rule with one premise

premise.description: A premise of an inference rule

conclusion.description: A conclusion of an inference rule

label.description: The label or name of an inference rule

german-font.description: A character in fraktur font. Fraktur is sometimes also called blackletter or gothic. In English it is called German rather then the font name. Most other locales do not need this rule.

parameters.%1: The character in bold fraktur font

german-font-bold.description: A character in bold fraktur font. Fraktur is sometimes also called blackletter or gothic. In English it is called German rather then the font name. Most other locales do not need this rule.

text.description: Text that needs to be announced or pronounced differently (e.g., not translated)

reciprocal.description: A unit to the power of negative one

logarithm-base.description: If the base of the logarithm should be spoken differently then the normal subscript

overbar-enclose.description: If an expression marked with an overbar that is spoken with start and end markers

underbar-enclose.description: If an expression marked with an underbar that is spoken with start and end markers

squared-masculine.description: Squared if base is grammatically of masculine gender

squared-feminine.description: Squared if base is grammatically of feminine gender
